The paper proposes a method for learning causal graphical models, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of gradient-based optimization and binary adjacency matrices suggests a focus on deep learning and optimization techniques, which are often studied in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of score functions and model functions, which are commonly used in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on causal inference and structure learning suggests a potential fit with the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
